The paper discusses the use of cognitive radios to exploit knowledge of primary transmissions, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves wireless communication networks (cs.NI) and cognitive radio networks (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the need for feedback and estimation, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of fading channels on data rates, which involves signal processing (cs.MM).
